WEBVTT

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.800
Hi everyone, my name is Sanjeev Thiyagarajan, and I will be your instructor for this course.

2
00:00:04.800 --> 00:00:09.480
In this course, I'm going to teach you how to build APIs in Python using a very popular

3
00:00:09.480 --> 00:00:16.200
framework called FastAPI, which makes it incredibly easy to build highly performant APIs in Python.

4
00:00:16.200 --> 00:00:22.040
Now, through this course, we're going to learn about common conventions when building APIs.

5
00:00:22.040 --> 00:00:26.879
We'll dive into the ins and outs of FastAPI, as well as learn how to read and write data

6
00:00:26.879 --> 00:00:29.320
to a PostgreSQL database.

7
00:00:29.320 --> 00:00:32.799
We'll also cover how to implement authentication within our API.

8
00:00:32.799 --> 00:00:39.279
So users can not only sign up, but also log in by utilizing JSON Web Tokens.

9
00:00:39.279 --> 00:00:43.400
And in this course, we're not going to just cover building APIs, we're going to learn

10
00:00:43.400 --> 00:00:45.020
a lot more than that.

11
00:00:45.020 --> 00:00:51.040
We're also going to cover how to properly test our APIs using a tool called Pytest.

12
00:00:51.040 --> 00:00:54.040
We'll also learn how to handle database migrations.

13
00:00:54.040 --> 00:00:58.000
And we'll learn how to deploy your application to two different platforms.

14
00:00:58.000 --> 00:01:02.099
That includes deploying to an Ubuntu server as well as Heroku.

15
00:01:02.099 --> 00:01:05.919
On top of that, I'm going to show you guys how to dockerize your application so it can

16
00:01:05.919 --> 00:01:07.860
run within a Docker container.

17
00:01:07.860 --> 00:01:12.379
And we're going to build a CI/CD pipeline so that we can automate the testing and deployment

18
00:01:12.379 --> 00:01:13.800
of our application.

19
00:01:13.800 --> 00:01:17.699
So by the end of this course, you will have a solid understanding of how to build robust

20
00:01:17.699 --> 00:01:21.099
APIs and how to properly test and deploy them.

21
00:01:21.099 --> 00:01:25.260
So whether you're building a back end for a web app, or creating an API for a machine

22
00:01:25.260 --> 00:01:28.980
learning model, you'll have all the tools you'll need to get up and running.

23
00:01:28.980 --> 00:01:30.459
So we've got a lot to learn.

24
00:01:30.459 --> 00:01:33.220
Let's get right to it and see what we'll be building in this course.
